Problem:
&nbsp; Cleanup finds 1 expired session EVERY cycle → same row
&nbsp;
Causes:
&nbsp; 1. ended\_at was NULL → WHERE clause matches repeatedly
&nbsp; 2. In-memory runner still shows status="running"
&nbsp; 3. Log fires even for already-known expired sessions

Fixes:
&nbsp; Website\_With\_DB.py:
&nbsp;   - Add AND ended\_at IS NULL to expiry UPDATE
&nbsp;   - Track already-expired session\_ids to suppress repeat logs
&nbsp;   - Call set\_session\_status\_in\_memory after expiring DB rows
&nbsp;   - Only log when expired\_count > 0 for NEWLY expired sessions

&nbsp; service.py:
&nbsp;   - \_mark\_auto\_run\_session\_status always calls
&nbsp;     set\_session\_status\_in\_memory to keep DB+memory in sync
&nbsp;   - Use COALESCE(ended\_at, CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP) to never
&nbsp;     overwrite an existing ended\_at

&nbsp; Heartbeat endpoint:
&nbsp;   - Add AND status IN ('running','started') guard
&nbsp;   - Prevents refreshing last\_accessed on expired rows


